
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to dynamically add nodes from a source to a destination node. It uses the [add] slot to append nodes from the [attachments] node inside the [.arguments] node to the children of the [.entity] node. The [get-nodes] slot retrieves the nodes from the specified path, and the [add] slot appends these nodes to the destination node's children collection.
add:x:@.entity/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/attachments/*
